'''James McFadden''' is the writer of over a dozen articles for ''[[The Official Star Wars Fact File]]'', as well as the [[Hyperspace: The Official Star Wars Fan Club|Hyperspace]]-exclusive ''[[The Forgotten War: The Nagai and the Tofs]]'', and ''[[Convenient Daily Departures: The History of Star Tours]]'' for the [[Star Wars Blog]]. He also created the backstory of the [[Eddicus-class planetary shuttle/Legends|''Eddicus''-class planetary shuttle]] appearing in the [[Databank (original)|Databank]], through the ''[[What's The Story?]]'' feature of [[StarWars.com]]'s [[Hyperspace: The Official Star Wars Fan Club|Hyperspace]].

He is the creator of [http://www.myuselessknowledge.com/sw JMM's Star Wars Chronology] website and co-founder of the [http://www.myuselessknowledge.com/swfa Star Wars Fanboy Association]. The [[JMM assassin droid|JMM]] espionage [[Droid/Legends|droid]] was named after him by fellow member [[Abel G. Peña]].

McFadden is also an avid ''G.I. Joe'' fan, and created and maintains [http://www.myuselessknowledge.com/joe JMM's G.I. Joe Comics Home Page].

{{Bio-stub}}

